<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. HOSTAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is in response to the story of the U.S. hostages in Lebanon (Part A, March 
16). 
</P>
<P>
On the biography list of the eight hostages, there were two mistakes on Alann 
Steen's background: 
</P>
<P>
1) He didn't meet and marry a professor from a Virginia university; he met and 
married a professor named Virginia at Beirut University where he taught and was 
abducted. 
</P>
<P>
2) Humboldt State University is not in Boston, it is in Arcata, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
Alann Steen is my father and I would like to see The Times get the facts 
straight. 
</P>
<P>
For future articles, Steen has a 1-year-old grandson named Jordan Alann 
Scardino he doesn't even know about. 
</P>
<P>
JACKIE STEEN SCARDINO 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
