<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NEW OWNERSHIP TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM LINDGREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHAIRMAN AND MANAGING PARTNER 
</P>
<P>
Tom Werner, partner in the Carsey-Werner Co. Werner is co-creator and executive 
producer of television's "The Cosby Show" and "Roseanne" and holds the latter 
title on "A Different World" and "Grand." "Cosby," "World" and "Grand" are on 
NBC and "Roseanne" is on ABC. All are popular family entertainment shows. 
</P>
<P>
VICE CHAIRMEN 
</P>
<P>
Goldsmith, chairman and chief executive officer, Republic Pictures. Goldsmith 
is also director of City National Bank and is a member of the board of 
governors of Cedars-Sinai Medical Center. Republic Pictures is a production and 
distribution company for television and home videos. It is known for its 
television series "Beauty and the Beast" and its extensive library, including 
"Bonanza" and "High Noon." 
</P>
<P>
Art Engel, president of Southwest Marine. Engel also runs the San Diego Harbor 
Excursion and the Old Ferry Landing, a shopping center in Coronado, and serves 
on the board of directors of the San Diego Port Tenants Assn. Southwest Marine 
has the largest network of ship-repair facilities on the West Coast. 
</P>
<P>
Art Rivkin, director of San Diego Trust &amp; Savings. Rivkin also owns R Group 
Management, which owns a radio station in Palm Springs and other investments. 
Rivkin was the president and owner of Coca-Cola Bottling Co. of San Diego 
before selling it in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
OTHER PARTNERS 
</P>
<P>
Malin Burnham, chairman of John Burnham &amp; Co. and First National Bank. 
Burnham is also the president of the Sail America Foundation, the syndicate 
that won the America's Cup for the San Diego Yacht Club. In addition, Burnham 
chairs the La Jolla Cancer Research Foundation, is a trustee of Stanford 
University and of the San Diego Hall of Champions, and is director of the 
Greater San Diego Sports Assn. (GSDSA). 
</P>
<P>
Jack Goodall Jr., chairman, president and CEO of Foodmaker Inc. Goodall is 
founder and director of Grossmont Bank, a director of the GSDSA, a chairman of 
the Child Abuse Prevention Foundation and a trustee of the University of San 
Diego and of Mercy Hospital. Foodmaker owns 970 Jack in the Box and 210 Chi-Chi 
restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
Leon Parma, president and owner of Coast Distributing Co. Parma is founder and 
chairman of La Jolla Bank &amp; Trust Co. He is a former president of the GSDSA 
and the Holiday Bowl, and was the first task force chairman of Super Bowl XXII 
in San Diego. Coast is the San Diego distributor of Anheuser-Busch products. 
</P>
<P>
L. Robert Payne, president of Mission Valley Associates Inc. and part-owner of 
Doubletree Hotel in San Diego. Payne is president-elect of the Holiday Bowl. 
Formerly, he was a chairman for San Diego County's Super Bowl Task Force in 
1988, president of the GSDSA and director of the Hall of Champions and Mercy 
Hospital Foundation. Mission Valley Associates is a real-estate development and 
investment company. 
</P>
<P>
Ernest Rady, chairman and president of American Assets Inc. Rady is also 
chairman of Insurance Co. of the West and Children's Hospital and director of 
Western Financial Savings Bank. American Assets is a real-estate development 
and investment firm. 
</P>
<P>
Scott Wolfe, partner in the law firm Latham &amp; Watkins. Wolfe helped put the 
group together and assisted in its negotiations with the Padres. He is also a 
trustee of Children's Hospital and La Jolla Cancer Research Foundation.JIM 
LINDGREN 
</P>
