<P>
GETTING READY FOR THE NEXT ONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors has proclaimed April as "Earthquake 
Preparedness Month" and has planned a number of activities. 
</P>
<P>
Included are a series of earthquake expositions featuring the Yogi Bear School 
House, fire engines, helicopters, hazardous materials and paramedic units, and 
emergency communications equipment. 
</P>
<P>
The dates, locations and times are: noon to 4 p.m. Saturday, Pacific Design 
Center, 8687 Melrose, West Hollywood; noon to 4 p.m. April 14, Lakewood Mall, 
Lakewood and Del Amo boulevards, Lakewood; noon to 4 p.m. April 21, Santa Anita 
Fashion Park, 400 S. Baldwin Ave., Arcadia, and 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. April 28 and 
29, Palmdale City Hall, 708 E. Palmdale Blvd., Palmdale. 
</P>
