<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONSERVING WATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Barbara and Ventura are now on mandatory water rationing. How long will 
it take for other Southland municipalities to implement such plans to save 
water? 
</P>
<P>
According to recent articles in The Times, (water) use is divided up 
accordingly: one-third for private residences, one-third for business and 
construction, and one-third for remaining needs. Waste runs rampant in Costa 
Mesa and especially in Newport Beach, where streams, small lakes and automatic 
sprinklers in complexes can be seen running into storm drains. Newport Beach 
recently reported daily usage of 18.5 million gallons for 100,000-plus 
residents. How absurd! 
</P>
<P>
EDWARD PFIRRMANN 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa 
</P>
</TEXT>
