</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg LeMond, world cycling champion, will be out of action for at least a month 
because of an unidentified virus infection, his French team Z said. 
</P>
<P>
LeMond, winner of last year's Tour de France, has returned to the United States 
to rest and will probably resume cycling May 6 in the Tour de Trump before 
returning to Europe for the Giro d'Italia, according to team Z officials. 
</P>
