<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BOAT DRIVER KILLED; RACE CONTINUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A driver in the Parker, Ariz., Enduro Classic was thrown from his power boat 
and killed during Sunday's three-hour marathon on the Colorado River near this 
border community opposite California. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said Dave Griffith, a deputy sheriff from Hawthorne, Nev., was thrown 
over the left forward portion of the boat when it hooked in the north turn of a 
two-mile loop. Griffith lost his crash helmet as he hit the water and was sent 
cartwheeling, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
A caution flag was displayed as emergency teams removed his body from the 
water, but the race continued. 
</P>
<P>
The race lasted seven hours last year, but was shortened because of insurance 
problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
