<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ben Johnson will be barred from Grand Prix and other invitational track meets 
in England, even after his two-year suspension for steroid use ends in 
September. 
</P>
<P>
The Amateur Athletic Assn., which governs the sport in England, said the ban 
will apply to any athlete found guilty of drug use by national or international 
federations. 
</P>
