<TEXT>
<P>
Construction Spending Up: The Commerce Department reported that spending on 
residential, non-residential and government construction projects all increased 
in February, helped for the second straight month by mild weather over much of 
the country. The department said construction spending rose 2.6% to a 
seasonally adjusted annual rate of $436.5 billion. That followed a revised 2.5% 
jump in January. 
</P>
