</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
T-Bill Rates Fall: The Treasury sold $8 billion of new three-month bills at an 
average discount rate of 7.83%, down from 7.85% last week. 
</P>
<P>
Another $8 billion of new six-month bills was sold at an average discount rate 
of 7.81%, down from 7.83% last week. The new discount rates understate the 
actual return to investors -- 8.10% for three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill 
selling for $9,802.10, and 8.24% for a six-month bill selling for $9,605.20. 
The discount rate reflects the price discount received when government 
securities are purchased at less than face value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
