<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: INCOMNET REPORTS LOSS FOR QUARTER, GAIN FOR YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Incomnet Inc. of Westlake Village, which operates a computerized auto parts 
trading network, lost $156,688 in the fourth quarter that ended Dec. 31, 
despite a 137% jump in revenues to $919,528. 
</P>
<P>
In the year-earlier quarter, Incomnet had net income of $235,335 on revenues of 
$388,315. 
</P>
<P>
For the year that ended in December, Incomnet reported net income of $228,766, 
compared with a $41,687 loss in 1988. Revenues rose 70% to $2.7 million from 
$1.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
Sam D. Schwartz, Incomnet's president, said the loss in the fourth quarter 
reflected a $168,778 charge to write off obsolete plant and equipment. The 
company, however, still managed to report a profit for the year, Schwartz said, 
because of an increased emphasis on marketing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
