<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Free Tickets in Paris: Mayor Jacques Chirac of Paris is giving out two theater 
tickets for the price of one this week in an attempt to lure Parisians back 
into the city's 115 theaters. Although Paris boasts 100,000 seats in theaters, 
attendance has plummeted in recent years, due in part to the increasing 
popularity of television and movies, and theater ticket prices that can run 
more than $50 each. The giveaway program starts today and will last three days. 
BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
