<P>
Perahia Won't Play: Pianist Murray Perahia, scheduled to play a recital in the 
Dorothy Chandler Pavilion of the Music Center tonight, has the flu and has 
canceled his appearance, according to a spokesperson for the Los Angeles 
Philharmonic, sponsor of the event. Ticketholders may obtain refunds at the 
Philharmonic box office, or write Box Office, 135 N. Grand, Los Angeles 90012. 
BETH KLEID 
