<P>
GM EXPECTED TO NAME NEW CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Motors Corp. has scheduled a news conference in Detroit this morning at 
which officials are expected to announce that Robert C. Stempel will succeed 
Roger B. Smith as the chairman of the world's largest industrial company. 
Stempel is currently president of GM. Smith, who has run GM for a decade, is 
scheduled to take mandatory retirement in August and has been preparing the 
line of succession for months. 
</P>
