<P>
BLAZE DESTROYS VACANT WAREHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire that blanketed much of the downtown business district with black smoke 
ravaged an earthquake-damaged warehouse. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported in the blaze at the four-story brick building at 6th 
and Bluxome streets. The cause of the fire was under investigation. A fire 
spokesman said the building, which suffered damage in the October quake that 
killed 67 people in Northern California, was empty "as far as we know." 
</P>
