<TEXT>
<P>
A series of fiery explosions rocked a Marine Corps maintenance facility, 
sending plumes of smoke 200 feet into the desert sky, officials and witnesses 
said. "We know there was an explosion to a warehouse and we know there were no 
injuries or casualties," said Sgt. Bill Bokholt, public affairs deputy for the 
Marine Corps Logistics Base. The explosions sparked a massive fire at a 
warehouse on the Yermo Annex, which took 90 minutes to control, Bokholt said. 
