<HEADLINE>
<P>
MINE KILLS SOLDIER IN LEBANESE ZONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KIRYAT SHEMONA, Israel 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A member of the Israeli-backed South Lebanon Army was killed Monday in a 
land-mine blast near the Lebanese town of Beit Yahoun, military officials said. 
</P>
<P>
They said that at least one other member of the patrol was wounded by the 
explosion inside Israel's self-declared security zone, a strip of Lebanese 
territory north of the Israeli border. 
</P>
<P>
The zone is patrolled by Israeli troops and the South Lebanon Army, which is 
paid and equipped by Israel to protect its northern frontier against guerrilla 
attacks. 
</P>
