<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: NO-HITTERS ARE THE NORM, NOT EXCEPTION, FOR AKAU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ARA NAJARIAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENA PARK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shannon Akau of Buena Park High School pitched two no-hitters last week, which 
surprised no one. 
</P>
<P>
Akau, The Times' Athlete of the Week, is a threat to pitch a no-hitter every 
time out. Dating to March 23, she had pitched three consecutive no-hitters 
until giving up four hits in a 7-2 victory over Walnut Friday. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't feel (the consecutive no-hitters are) surprising. It's not even a 
topic," Buena Park Coach Brenda Sapp said. "She's a power pitcher. I can tell 
you she's up there with (former Valencia pitcher Michele) Granger. I believe 
she can throw with any college pitcher." 
</P>
<P>
Akau has pitched five no-hitters this season and has a 7-1 record, helping 
Buena Park to an 8-1-1 start. In 56 innings, Akau has 89 strikeouts and only 
two walks. Her earned-run average is 0.25. 
</P>
<P>
Tuesday, Akau pitched her second consecutive no-hitter, striking out 15 and 
walking a batter in the fourth inning, in a 3-0 victory over Savanna. 
</P>
<P>
The third one came Wednesday, when she had 11 strikeouts and a walk (in the 
first inning) in a 12-0 victory over Dominguez. That game was stopped after 
five innings because of the mercy rule. 
</P>
<P>
"The pitching has 50% to 80% to do with winning," Sapp said, "but without the 
bats we couldn't win a game for Shannon." 
</P>
<P>
In three games last week, Buena Park supported Akau with 21 runs. And Akau has 
been doing her part from the batter's box too. 
</P>
<P>
She went three for three against Dominguez, including a three-run home run in 
the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
"I consider myself a contact hitter," Akau said. "I don't think being a pitcher 
helps me anticipate what the other will throw." 
</P>
<P>
TOP PERFORMERS 
</P>
<P>
Kaci Keffer won the 400-meter race (58.66 seconds), the 300 hurdles (46.43) and 
anchored the winning 1,600 relay team to lead Woodbridge to the girls' title at 
the Valencia Invitational Saturday. Also for Woodbridge, Cathi Peck won the 800 
(2:23.37) and 3,200 (11:27.84). 
</P>
<P>
Rae Rice pitched a no-hitter and had 13 strikeouts in leading Fountain Valley 
to a 2-0 softball victory over Sunny Hills Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Robin Russell of Newport Harbor pitched her first career no-hitter in a 2-0 
victory over Long Beach Wilson Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Stephanie Smith pitched her fourth no-hitter of the season, striking out nine, 
to lead Garden Grove to a 3-0 victory over Bolsa Grande Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Shannon Akau 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park High School 
</P>
<P>
* Position: Pitcher 
</P>
<P>
* Height, Weight, Class: 5-3, 110, Senior 
</P>
<P>
* Last Week: Akau pitched no-hitters Tuesday and Wednesday, her second and 
third in a row and fifth this season. 
</P>
<P>
* Season: In 56 innings, Akau has a 7-1 record, with 89 strikeouts, two walks 
and a 0.25 earned-run average. Akau is hitting .370 with one home run and three 
RBIs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
