<P>
MCDONNELL DOUGLAS TEAMSTERS OVERWHELMINGLY OK 3-YEAR PACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Teamsters at McDonnell Douglas Corp.'s Southern California plants ratified a 
3-year labor contract after seven months of negotiation, a spokesman for the 
aerospace company said today. 
</P>
<P>
"I just got word this morning," Jim Reed said from the aerospace company's 
corporate headquarters in St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
He said the vote took place Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The contract, covering 250 Teamsters from Local 692, was approved by a vote of 
156 to 7. The Teamsters International had sanctioned a strike to occur as early 
as today. 
</P>
<P>
Local 692 represents truck drivers, chauffeurs and railroad freight handlers 
whose wages have averaged about $15 an hour. Members carry and unload parts and 
major aerospace components to the corporation's Douglas Aircraft Co. facilities 
in Long Beach, Torrance and Carson, and McDonnell Douglas Space Systems in 
Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Douglas spokesman Don Hanson said the pact is similar to a contract the company 
signed in December with its machinists union. That contract provides a 5 1/2% 
pay raise in the first year and 3% increases in each of the second and third 
years. It also provides for a 4% annual lump-sum bonus for each worker, based 
on the worker's total yearly wage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
