<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
WAS HE TEED OFF? YOU BET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STOCKHOLM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The game of golf requires a cool mind and a steady hand. 
</P>
<P>
But even the keenest of golfers can sometimes raise his club in anger. 
</P>
<P>
A Swedish player recently was practicing his swing on a small airfield outside 
the southern Swedish town of Hoganas when a groundsman drove up on a tractor 
and told him to stop. 
</P>
<P>
The golfer, angered by the interruption, smashed the side windows of the 
tractor with his club. 
</P>
<P>
Groundsman Allan Jonsson escaped unharmed, according to the Swedish news agency 
TT, but he reported the incident to the police, who charged the golfer -- with 
violation of aviation laws. 
</P>
</TEXT>
